{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/Miniconda/01-Install-Miniconda/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"c7e140fd-6a96-5bc4-a1a3-6c7efac8c0ac","html":"<p>This guide will show you how to install the latest version of Miniconda. Miniconda is a lightweight version of Anaconda: a virtual environment manager for Python.</p>\n<h2>Download Install Script</h2>\n<h3>Linux</h3>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      wget https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh -O ~/miniconda.sh\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h3>Mac</h3>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      wget https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-latest-MacOSX-x86_64.sh -O ~/miniconda.sh\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Install Minconda</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      sh ~/miniconda.sh -b -f -p  $HOME/.miniconda\n\nrm ~/miniconda.sh\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Setting up your shell</h2>\n<p>If you don't want the conda base environment (you may not want this because as of now there are conflicts with later versions of Python and npm)</p>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      conda config --set auto_activate_base false\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<p>The first time you run it, it'll create a ./condarc in your home directory with that setting to override the default.</p>\n<p>Now you can initialize your shell with the following command:</p>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      conda init $SHELL\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<p>Now close your terminal and open a new one and your conda environment should be fully configured.</p>","excerpt":"This guide will show you how to install the latest version of Miniconda. Miniconda is a lightweight version of Anaconda: a virtualâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"How to install Miniconda","tags":["miniconda"],"image":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/fa7b659b02c579ef29c4beab0d4328f2/9cf42/miniconda.jpg"},"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7747747747747749,"src":"/static/fa7b659b02c579ef29c4beab0d4328f2/e3fce/miniconda.jpg","srcSet":"/static/fa7b659b02c579ef29c4beab0d4328f2/81890/miniconda.jpg 197w,\n/static/fa7b659b02c579ef29c4beab0d4328f2/b7e42/miniconda.jpg 393w,\n/static/fa7b659b02c579ef29c4beab0d4328f2/e3fce/miniconda.jpg 786w,\n/static/fa7b659b02c579ef29c4beab0d4328f2/16310/miniconda.jpg 1024w","sizes":"(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/Miniconda/01-Install-Miniconda/","prev":{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/Jupyter/01-jupyter-remote/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Setting up a Remote Jupyter Lab Server","tags":["jupyter"]}}},"next":{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/Spring/01-Intro-to-Springboot/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Intro to Spring Boot","tags":["spring"]}}}}}}